label.value: Adenosarcoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of adenosarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Adenosarcoma pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: No regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of adenosarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Distant metastasis (excluding adnexa, pelvic and abdominal tissues). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of adenosarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Adenosarcoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of adenosarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Fallopian Tube Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: (Any T, Any N, M1).  M1: Distant metastasis (excludes metastasis within the peritoneal cavity). (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Adenosarcoma cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Distant metastasis (excluding adnexa, pelvic and abdominal tissues). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage 0 Uterine Corpus Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  This staging applies to carcinomas and carcinosarcomas.  FIGO no longer includes Stage 0 (Tis). (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage I Uterine Corpus Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: I (T1, N0, M0); IA: (T1a, N0, M0); IB (T1b, N0, M0). T1: Tumor confined to corpus uteri. T1a: Tumor limited to the endometrium or invades less than one-half of the myometrium. T1b: Tumor invades one-half or more of the myometrium. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. This staging applies to carcinomas and carcinosarcomas. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Uterine Corpus Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0.  T2: Tumor invades stromal connective tissue of the cervix but does not extend beyond uterus.  Endocervical glandular involvement only should be considered as Stage I and not as Stage II.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  This staging applies to carcinomas and carcinosarcomas. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Uterine Corpus Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: III (T3, N0, M0); IIIA (T3a, N0, M0); IIIB (T3b, N0, M0); IIIC (T1-T3, N1/N2, M0); IIIC1 (T1-T3, N1, M0); IIIC2 (T1-T3, N2, M0). T3: Tumor involves serosa and/or adnexa, vagina, or parametrial tissue. T3a: Tumor involves serosa and/or adnexa (direct extension or metastasis). T3b: Tumor involves vagina (direct extension or metastasis) or parametrial tissue. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Regional lymph node metastasis to pelvic lymph nodes. N2: Regional lymph node metastasis to para-aortic lymph nodes, with or without positive pelvic lymph nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis. This staging applies to carcinomas and carcinosarcomas. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Uterine Corpus Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: (T4, Any N, M0); IVB: (Any T, Any N, M1). T4: Tumor invades bladder mucosa and/or bowel mucosa (bullous edema is not sufficient to classify a tumor as T4).  M0: No distant metastasis. M1: Distant metastasis (includes metastasis to inguinal lymph nodes, intraperitoneal disease, or lung, liver, or bone.  It excludes metastasis to para-aortic lymph nodes, vagina, pelvic serosa, or adnexa). This staging applies to carcinomas and carcinosarcomas. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Ovarian cancer and primary peritoneal carcinoma are surgically/pathologically staged malignancies. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Synovial Neoplasm

value.value: A benign or malignant soft tissue neoplasm arising exclusively from the synovial membrane.  Examples include the diffuse giant cell tumor of tendon sheath, localized giant cell tumor of tendon sheath, and malignant giant cell tumor of tendon sheath.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer limited to ovaries (one or both). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer limited to one ovary; capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface.  No malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer limited to both ovaries; capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface.  No malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma limited to one or both ovaries with any of the following: capsule ruptured, tumor on ovarian surface, malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma involving one or both ovaries with pelvic extension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with extension and/or implants on uterus and/or tube(s).  No malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with extension to and/or implants on other pelvic tissues.  No malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with pelvic extension and/or implants (T2a or T2b) with malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lymphangioma

value.value: A benign lesion composed of dilated lymphatic channels. Painless swelling is the usual clinical manifestation.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma involving one or both ovaries with microscopically confirmed peritoneal metastasis outside the pelvis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with microscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis (no macroscopic tumor). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with macroscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis more than 2 cm in greatest dimension and/or regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma without regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with distant metastasis (excludes peritoneal metastasis). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Paraneoplastic Opsoclonus Ataxia

value.value: Ataxia associated with chaotic multidirectional conjugate eye movements secondary to metastatic tumors to cerebellum.  The most common malignant tumor associated with this paraneoplastic syndrome is lung carcinoma. (NCI)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ovarian cancer or primary peritoneal carcinoma with distant metastasis (excludes peritoneal metastasis). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Fallopian Tube Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of fallopian tube cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Histologic confirmation of primary disease with complete evaluation of the abdomen and pelvis is required. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Fallopian Tube Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of fallopian tube cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Fallopian Tube Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of fallopian tube cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Fallopian Tube Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Fallopian tube cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
